# Atlas CertOps
## System Architecture Guide

Version: 1.0

Document Classification:
Internal / Customer Administrator

Owner:
Atlas & Else

---

# 1. Purpose

This document describes the logical and physical architecture of Atlas CertOps.

It provides administrators, engineers, auditors, and implementation teams with an understanding of how the platform is structured and how major components interact.

---

# 2. Design Principles

Atlas CertOps is designed around the following principles:

• Cloud-first
• API-first
• Secure by default
• Stateless application tier
• Horizontal scalability
• High availability
• Least-privilege access
• Comprehensive auditability
• Vendor-neutral integrations
• Modular service boundaries

---

# 3. High-Level Architecture

Client Layer
    │
    ▼
Web Application (React)
    │
HTTPS / TLS 1.3
    │
    ▼
Application API
    │
    ├── Authentication
    ├── Certificate Management
    ├── Reporting
    ├── Workflow Engine
    ├── Notifications
    ├── Audit Service
    ├── Integration Service
    │
    ▼
PostgreSQL Database
    │
    ▼
Encrypted Object Storage

